ZH: 他站在我的面前。
EN: He is standing in front of me.

ZH: 她站在镜子的面前。
EN: She is standing in front of the mirror.

ZH: 他在老板面前说了谎。
EN: He lied in front of the boss.

ZH: 我有一个机会站在世界面前。
EN: I have a chance to stand in front of the world.

ZH: 她在考试面前紧张得手都在发抖。
EN: She is so nervous in front of the exam that her hands are shaking.

ZH: 我们在历史的面前感到渺小。
EN: We feel small in front of history.

ZH: 在工作面前，他总是全力以赴。
EN: He always gives his all in front of work.

ZH: 面对失败的时候，不要气馁。
EN: Don't despair in the face of failure.

ZH: 面对挑战，我们有信心克服困难。
EN: Faced with challenges, we have confidence to overcome difficulties.

ZH: 在朋友面前，我总能放下所有的伪装。
EN: In front of friends, I can always let go of all pretenses.

ZH: 面对现实，我们必须做出选择。
EN: Faced with reality, we must make choices.

ZH: 在困难面前，我们需要团结一致。
EN: In the face of difficulties, we need to unite.

ZH: 他能够镇定地面对危险。
EN: He can face danger calmly.

ZH: 面对挑战，他总是勇往直前。
EN: Faced with challenges, he always moves forward bravely.

ZH: 在困境面前，我们要保持乐观。
EN: In the face of adversity, we must remain optimistic.

ZH: 面对失败，他不懈努力改正错误。
EN: Faced with failure, he tirelessly corrects his mistakes.

ZH: 我们要勇敢地面对自己内心的恐惧。
EN: We must bravely face our inner fears.

ZH: 面对困难，我们不能选择逃避。
EN: Faced with difficulties, we cannot choose to escape.

ZH: 在朋友面前，我们能够真实地表达自己。
EN: In front of friends, we can express ourselves truthfully.

ZH: 面对危险，他表现出了惊人的勇气。
EN: Faced with danger, he showed amazing courage.
